The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Bangalore, July 24: Britannia Industries today reported a net profit of Rs 36.1 crore for the quarter ended June 30, a 20 per cent increase over the year-ago period. The companys sales saw a 19 percent rise at Rs 576.9 crore, a company release said. Managing director Vinita Bali said, The company is focusing on strengthening the shape of its business and leveraging synergy benefits of recent acquisitions. 

 New Delhi, July 24: The Supreme Court has held that an insurance firm is liable to compensate for any damage of goods till it reaches the final destination. The judgement can lead to a hassle-free settlement of insurance claims.

 New Delhi, July 24: Power firms NHPC and PGCIL will get the navratna status soon. After that they will come out with their initial public offering, a government official said.

 Mumbai, July 24: Idea Cellulars board has approved formation of a wholly owned arm to hive off GSM towers and other passive infrastructure to monetise the assets and focus on core business.

 Bharti Airtel, R-Com and Tata Teleservices have already made similar announcements. 

 Calcutta, July 24: Aluminium company Indal said its merger with Hindalco would probably be completed by 2007-08. We plan to merge the Kollur plant in the near future, Indal chairman A.K. Agarwala said.




